d\": 247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999704377847, \"rank\": 2.956232588174422e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 309, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9955465311243747, \"rank\": 0.002462979613688574, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 350, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9977265863496925, \"rank\": 0.0016787866564975883, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French media reported five men raped the woman.\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 444, \"end\": 450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9977265863496925, \"rank\": 0.0016787866564975883, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement did not name the victim but said the alleged assault occurred overnight Friday, July 19, and that the woman then sought refuge in a Paris restaurant where firefighters provided emergency assistance and later took the victim to a hospital.\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 641, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999704377847, \"rank\": 2.956232588174422e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade said in a statement Wednesday that the Australian Embassy in Paris has sought to offer consular assistance to a citizen, who had been assaulted in the French capital.\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9760440289860963, \"rank\": 0.02453504164015622, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Embassy_of_Australia,_Washington,_D.C.\", \"score\": 0.7058375487871591, \"rank\": 0.288461538461511, \"text\": \"Australian Embassy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Embassy_of_Australia,_Washington,_D.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Embassy_of_Australia,_Washington,_D.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999704377847, \"rank\": 2.956232588174422e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 952, \"end\": 958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9977265863496925, \"rank\": 0.0016787866564975883, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We understand that this is a very traumatic experience and stand ready to provide assistance,\\\" the statement said.\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It did not provide any other information to protect the victim's privacy.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Reports in Australian media said the victim had initially planned to immediately return to Australia but later decided to stay in France.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1173, \"end\": 1183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9955465311243747, \"rank\": 0.002462979613688574, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9760440289860963, \"rank\": 0.02453504164015622, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1292, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9008608886240529, \"rank\": 0.07542494843875232, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It did not provide any other information due to privacy obligations.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris security authorities have been on high alert in the lead-up to the Olympic Games that kick off on Friday with an open-air ceremony on the River Seine.\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999704377847, \"rank\": 2.956232588174422e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1514, \"end\": 1525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The city is deploying 35,000 police officers daily for the Olympics, which run until August 11, with a peak of 45,000 for the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, 10,000 soldiers are taking part in security operations in the Paris region.\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999704377847, \"rank\": 2.956232588174422e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Take your experience further with Premium access.Thought-provoking Opinions, Expert Analysis, In-depth Insights and other Member Only Benefits  Already a Member?Sign In Now  The Tribune, now published from Chandigarh, started publication on February 2, 1881, in Lahore (now in Pakistan).\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 2049, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1968, \"end\": 1978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0498248769361943e-17, \"text\": \"Chandigarh\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\"}, {\"begin\": 2024, \"end\": 2030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.1245289032775269e-13, \"text\": \"Lahore\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\"}, {\"begin\": 2039, \"end\": 2047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999990344845286, \"rank\": 8.600036702431219e-07, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was started by Sardar Dyal Singh Majithia, a public-spirited philanthropist, and is run by a trust comprising five eminent persons as trustees.The Tribune, the largest selling English daily in North India, publishes news and views without any bias or prejudice of any kind.\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2068, \"end\": 2074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.801154518349428e-28, \"text\": \"Sardar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\"}, {\"begin\": 2075, \"end\": 2094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dyal Singh Majithia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Restraint and moderation, rather than agitational language and partisanship, are the hallmarks of the newspaper.\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is an independent newspaper in the real sense of the term.The Tribune has two sister publications, Punjabi Tribune (in Punjabi) and Dainik Tribune (in Hindi).\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2542, \"end\": 2557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punjabi Tribune\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\"}, {\"begin\": 2562, \"end\": 2569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\", \"score\": 0.8601818892663889, \"rank\": 0.16140785372579422, \"text\": \"Punjabi\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_langua